---
const year = new Date().getFullYear();
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
		<title>agentskillforge.com - FAQ</title>
		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Frequently asked questions about long-running workflow agents and how Agent Skill Forge helps teams build and evolve agentic systems."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<header class="sticky top-0 z-50 border-b border-brand-secondary/10 bg-brand-background/80 backdrop-blur">
			<div class="container flex h-16 items-center justify-between">
				<a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-3 font-semibold tracking-tight">
					<img
						src="/agentskillforge-logo-asf-alt2.png"
						alt="agentskillforge logo"
						class="h-7 w-auto"
					/>
					<span class="text-brand-secondary">agentskillforge.com</span>
				</a>
				<nav class="hidden items-center gap-6 text-sm md:flex">
					<a class="text-brand-secondary/70 hover:text-brand-secondary" href="/">Home</a>
					<a class="text-brand-secondary/70 hover:text-brand-secondary" href="/services">Services</a>
					<a class="text-brand-secondary/70 hover:text-brand-secondary" href="/faq">FAQ</a>
					<a
						class="rounded-lg bg-brand-secondary px-4 py-2 text-white hover:bg-brand-secondary/90"
						href="/contact">Contact</a>
				</nav>
			</div>
		</header>

		<main id="top">
			<section id="faq" class="border-t border-brand-secondary/10 bg-brand-background">
				<div class="container py-14">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight">FAQ</h2>
					<div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">What exactly is a “long-running workflow agent” (and how is it different from a chatbot)?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									A long-running workflow agent is designed to stay useful over time by operating as part of an ongoing process (not just answering questions once). It’s built to work toward a business outcome, then improve and evolve with your operating style.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">Where will the agent run (your servers vs our servers)?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>You own the environment where you agent runs. We can deploy an environment on your behalf or host at your site depending on your requirements.</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">What systems can the agent connect to?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We connect agents to the systems you already use, so they can support real workflows end-to-end (for example, the tools your team relies on day-to-day).
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How do you train the agent to match our business rules and operating style?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We initially work in partnership with you to train the agent so it aligns with your business rules and operating style. Our goal is to empower your team to take full ownership over time, with the tools and training needed to independently train, refine, and manage the agents yourselves.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How do you keep agents safe and accountable (governance, approvals, audit logs)?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We build governance and auditability into the system so your team can review what the agent is doing, apply rules, and maintain accountability.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">Can we start with a pilot first? How do you choose the first workflow?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									Yes. We typically start with workflows that benefit from repetition and structure, and that map clearly to business goals. Then we scope, train, and ship a pilot.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">Do you offer ready-made agents, or do you build custom ones for us?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>Both approaches can be a fit. We offer:</p>
								<ul class="list-disc pl-5">
									<li>Consulting to identify what to automate first and how to design for outcomes</li>
									<li>Ready-made agentic systems you can configure</li>
									<li>Pre-trained agents tailored to your domain and constraints</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How long does it take to go from the intro call to a working pilot?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									The timing depends on the workflow you choose and how it needs to be scoped and trained. We’ll confirm an approach and plan based on your goals during onboarding.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">What data do you need from us, and how do you handle sensitive information?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We start by aligning on what the pilot needs to use. Because the agents run inside your environment, your governance and auditability remain in-house, with responsibility and control staying clear.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How do you support ongoing improvements after the pilot?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									Since the goal is a long-running workflow agent, we design for continuous improvement. After the pilot, we can iterate and expand the system as your team’s needs evolve.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">What’s included in staff enablement?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>Staff enablement includes training, rollout support, and guidance so your team can use and govern the agents safely and effectively.</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">What do you mean by “portability and exit rights”?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We design the system so responsibility stays with you. That means governance, auditability, and the ability to continue operating (or transition) remain on your terms.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How does pricing work?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									Pricing depends on what you choose as a starting point (consulting, ready-made systems, pre-trained agents, and/or staff enablement) and the scope of the pilot and rollout. We’ll outline a plan after learning your goals and constraints.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">If the first workflow isn’t a fit, what happens next?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									We’ll adjust the pilot scope and move toward a workflow that better matches the value, constraints, and outcomes you want. The intent is to find a practical starting point and build from there.
								</p>
							</div>
						</details>

						<details class="group rounded-2xl border border-brand-secondary/10 bg-white px-6 py-4">
							<summary class="cursor-pointer list-none font-medium">How will this help my business (what outcomes can we expect)?</summary>
							<div class="mt-2 space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-brand-secondary/80">
								<p>
									Our goal is to turn agentic AI into practical, long-running workflow agents that help teams execute real work toward business goals. In most cases, you can expect:
								</p>
								<ul class="list-disc pl-5">
									<li>automation of structured, repeatable parts of workflows</li>
									<li>clearer governance and accountability</li>
									<li>staff enablement so your team can operate the system confidently</li>
									<li>a path to evolve from a pilot into ongoing workflows</li>
								</ul>
							</div>
						</details>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer class="border-t border-brand-secondary/10">
			<div class="container py-8 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
				<p class="text-sm text-brand-secondary/70">© {year} agentskillforge.com</p>
				<div class="flex gap-4 text-sm">
					<a class="text-brand-secondary/70 hover:text-brand-secondary" href="/">Back to home</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</footer>
	</body>
</html>
